        "---\n",
        "title: \"Lecture 02: Dynamic Movement Primitives\"\n",
        "execute:\n",
        "  enabled: true\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "Let $\\mathcal{Q} = \\mathbb{R}^{n}$ denote the configuration space.\n",
        "The simplest representation of robot motion (trajectory) data we can collect is a sequence of time-configuration pairs:\n",
        "\\begin{equation}\n",
        "\\big((t_1, q_1), (t_2, q_2), \\ldots, (t_N, q_N)\\big),\n",
        "\\end{equation}\n",
        "where $t_i \\in [0, T]$ denotes the time variable -- where $0=t_1 < t_2 < \\cdots < t_N=T$ with the terminal time $T$ \n",
        "-- and $q_i \\in \\mathcal{Q}$ is an $n$-dimensional vector.\n",
        "\n",
        "Given a single trajectory, the simplest robot learning problem\n",
        "is to learn a policy that maps the clock variable $t$ to an action so that \n",
        "the robot can reproduce the demonstrated trajectory.\n",
        "We consider desired position, velocity, and acceleration\n",
        "as actions, denoted by\n",
        "$a = (q_{\\mathrm{des}}, \\dot{q}_{\\mathrm{des}}, \\ddot{q}_{\\mathrm{des}})$.\n",
        "Then, a low-level controller, e.g., computed torque control, tracks this command.\n",
        "\n",
        "We require the policy to satisfy two criteria.\n",
        "First, it should drive the robot to the goal point\n",
        "$g := q_N$ (i.e., the terminal point of the demonstrated trajectory)\n",
        "as $t \\to \\infty$.\n",
        "Second, it should allow slight modulation of the goal point\n",
        "while preserving the overall shape of the trajectory.\n",
        "\n",
        "Dynamic Movement Primitives (DMP), inspired by the motor control of\n",
        "biological systems, have elegant formulation, guarantee convergence \n",
        "to a given target, are sufficiently flexible to create complex behaviors, \n",
        "and can be learned from data using efficient algorithms.\n",
        "\n",
        "At $t = 0$, initialize the desired state as\n",
        "\\begin{equation}\n",
        "\\big(q_{\\mathrm{des}}(0), \\dot{q}_{\\mathrm{des}}(0), \\ddot{q}_{\\mathrm{des}}(0)\\big) = \\big(q_1, 0, 0\\big),\n",
        "\\end{equation}\n",
        "and a continuous-time DMP can be written as:\n",
        "\\begin{equation}\n",
        "\\ddot{q}_{\\mathrm{des}}(t) = K\\big(g - q_{\\mathrm{des}}(t)\\big) - D \\dot{q}_{\\mathrm{des}}(t) + f(t;\\theta),\n",
        "\\end{equation}\n",
        "where $K, D \\in \\mathbb{R}^{n \\times n}$ are positive-definite stiffness and damping gain matrices.\n",
        "The function $f(t;{\\theta}) \\in \\mathbb{R}^{n}$ is parameterized by $\\theta \\in \\Theta$.\n",
        "This parametric forcing term modulates the trajectory shape beyond linear\n",
        "mass-spring-damper dynamics.\n",
        "\n",
        "The forcing term can be defined as a normalized weighted sum of\n",
        "$N$ radial basis functions (RBFs):\n",
        "\\begin{align}\n",
        "    f(t;\\theta) &= \\left(\\frac{\\sum_{i=1}^{N} \\theta_i \\psi_i(s)}{\\sum_{i=1}^{N} \\psi_i(s)}\\right)s, \\\\\n",
        "    \\psi_i(s) &= \\exp\\!\\left(-\\frac{(s - c_i)^2}{\\delta^2}\\right), \\\\\n",
        "    s(t) &= \\max\\!\\left(1 - \\frac{t}{T}, 0\\right).\n",
        "\\end{align}\n",
        "Here, $s$ is a phase variable that starts at $1$, decreases to $0$,\n",
        "and then remains at $0$. Each $\\theta_i \\in \\mathbb{R}^{n}$ is a learnable\n",
        "weight vector, and each $\\psi_i(s) \\in \\mathbb{R}$ is a scalar basis function.\n",
        "The basis centers are typically chosen as $c_i = \\frac{i-1}{N-1}$ with\n",
        "a shared width $\\delta = \\frac{1}{N-1}$.\n",
        "\n",
        "Using a forward-Euler discretization with time step $h$ and\n",
        "$t_k = kh$, the desired state is updated at each step $k$ as:\n",
        "\n",
        "\\begin{align}\n",
        "    \\ddot{q}_{\\mathrm{des}}^{k} &= K\\big(g - q_{\\mathrm{des}}^{k}\\big) - D\\dot{q}_{\\mathrm{des}}^{k} + f(t_k; \\theta), \\\\\n",
        "    \\dot{q}_{\\mathrm{des}}^{k+1} &= \\dot{q}_{\\mathrm{des}}^{k} + h\\,\\ddot{q}_{\\mathrm{des}}^{k}, \\\\\n",
        "    q_{\\mathrm{des}}^{k+1} &= q_{\\mathrm{des}}^{k} + h\\,\\dot{q}_{\\mathrm{des}}^{k}.\n",
        "\\end{align}\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {#exm-random-theta name=\"2D DMP Example with Random $\\theta$\"}\n",
        "<br>\n",
        "Consider a 2D DMP ($q \\in \\mathbb{R}^{2}$) with\n",
        "$q_1 = [-0.8, -0.6]^\\top$, $g = [1.0, 0.8]^\\top$, \n",
        "$K = 80I$, $D = 18I$, $T = 2.0$, and $h = 0.01$.\n",
        "Let $N = 30$ and sample a random parameter matrix\n",
        "$\\theta = [\\theta_1, \\ldots, \\theta_N] \\in \\mathbb{R}^{2 \\times N}$."
