        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "Now, we consider how to learn $\\theta$ from the demonstrated trajectory\n",
        "$\\big((t_i, q_i)\\big)_{i=1}^{M}$.\n",
        "Given the observed positions, we first estimate $\\dot{q}_i$ and $\\ddot{q}_i$\n",
        "(e.g., via finite differences), and then fit $\\theta$ so that the DMP dynamics\n",
        "reconstruct these accelerations along the demonstration.\n",
        "\n",
        "For each sample $i$, define the target forcing term and feature vector as\n",
        "\\begin{align}\n",
        "f_i^{\\star} &= \\ddot{q}_i - K(g - q_i) + D\\dot{q}_i, \\\\\n",
        "\\phi_i &= s_i\n",
        "\\begin{bmatrix}\n",
        "\\dfrac{\\psi_1(s_i)}{\\sum_{j=1}^{N}\\psi_j(s_i)} \\\\\n",
        "\\vdots \\\\\n",
        "\\dfrac{\\psi_N(s_i)}{\\sum_{j=1}^{N}\\psi_j(s_i)}\n",
        "\\end{bmatrix}\n",
        "\\in \\mathbb{R}^{N}.\n",
        "\\end{align}\n",
        "Then the regression model is\n",
        "\\begin{equation}\n",
        "f_i^{\\star} \\approx \\theta \\phi_i, \\qquad \\theta \\in \\mathbb{R}^{n \\times N}.\n",
        "\\end{equation}\n",
        "Stacking data as\n",
        "$F^{\\star} = [f_1^{\\star}, \\ldots, f_M^{\\star}] \\in \\mathbb{R}^{n \\times M}$\n",
        "and\n",
        "$\\Phi = [\\phi_1, \\ldots, \\phi_M] \\in \\mathbb{R}^{N \\times M}$,\n",
        "we obtain the ridge-regression solution\n",
        "\\begin{equation}\n",
        "\\theta^{\\star} = F^{\\star}\\Phi^{\\top}\\big(\\Phi\\Phi^{\\top} + \\lambda I\\big)^{-1},\n",
        "\\end{equation}\n",
        "where $\\lambda \\ge 0$ is a regularization coefficient.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {#exm-ridge-regression name=\"2D DMP Fit to an S-shaped Demonstration\"}\n",
        "<br>\n",
        "We now fit $\\theta$ from a synthetic 2D demonstration and visualize the results."
