        "<video src=\"imgs/02-dynamic-movement-primitives/dmp_goal_modulation_1x4.webm\" controls autoplay loop muted playsinline style=\"width:100%\"></video>\n",
        "::::\n",
        "\n",
        "Recall that this policy takes only the clock variable $t$ as input.\n",
        "That is, it has no sensory-feedback input.\n",
        "As a result, it is not robust to external disturbances: if the robot is pushed far away\n",
        "from the demonstrated trajectory, or if a temporal perturbation occurs\n",
        "(e.g., the robot is held still while time continues to flow),\n",
        "the desired state still advances and converges according to the internal clock.\n",
        "\n",
        "An alternative way to use a learned DMP model is to define the acceleration command\n",
        "directly from sensory feedback:\n",
        "\\begin{equation}\n",
        "    \\ddot{q}_{\\mathrm{des}} = K(g - q) - D\\dot{q} + f(t; \\theta),\n",
        "\\end{equation}\n",
        "where $(q,\\dot{q})$ is the proprioceptive state. \n",
        "This is still not fully robust to temporal disturbances because\n",
        "$f$ remains time-dependent.\n",
        "However, it typically leads to less dangerous behavior under\n",
        "a high-stiffness low-level position controller.\n",
        "See the example below:\n",
        "\n",
        ":::: {#exm-perturbation-comparison name=\"Clock-Only vs Feedback DMP Under Large Perturbation\"}"
      ],
      "id": "c08e0986"
